title: Alteration
terms.definition: Modifying the anatomic structure of a body part without affecting the function of the body part
terms.explanation: Principal purpose is to improve appearance

title: Bypass
terms.definition: Altering the route of passage of the contents of a tubular body part
terms.explanation: Rerouting contents of a body part to a downstream area of the normal route, to a similar route and body part, or to an abnormal route and dissimilar body part. Includes one or more anastomoses, with or without the use of a device

title: Change
terms.definition: Taking out or off a device from a body part and putting back an identical or similar device in or on the same body part without cutting or puncturing the skin or a mucous membrane
terms.explanation: All CHANGE procedures are coded using the approach EXTERNAL
includes: Urinary catheter change, gastrostomy tube change

title: Control
terms.definition: Stopping, or attempting to stop, postprocedural or other acute bleeding
includes: Control of post-prostatectomy hemorrhage, control of intracranial subdural hemorrhage, control of bleeding duodenal ulcer, control of retroperitoneal hemorrhage

title: Creation
terms.definition: Putting in or on biological or synthetic material to form a new body part that to the extent possible replicates the anatomic structure or function of an absent body part
terms.explanation: Used for gender reassignment surgery and corrective procedures in individuals with congenital anomalies
includes: Creation of vagina in a male, creation of right and left atrioventricular valve from common atrioventricular valve

title: Destruction
terms.definition: Physical eradication of all or a portion of a body part by the direct use of energy, force, or a destructive agent
terms.explanation: None of the body part is physically taken out
includes: Fulguration of rectal polyp, cautery of skin lesion

title: Detachment
terms.definition: Cutting off all or a portion of the upper or lower extremities
terms.explanation: The body part value is the site of the detachment, with a qualifier if applicable to further specify the level where the extremity was detached
includes: Below knee amputation, disarticulation of shoulder

title: Dilation
terms.definition: Expanding an orifice or the lumen of a tubular body part
terms.explanation: The orifice can be a natural orifice or an artificially created orifice. Accomplished by stretching a tubular body part using intraluminal pressure or by cutting part of the orifice or wall of the tubular body part

title: Division
terms.definition: Cutting into a body part, without draining fluids and/or gases from the body part, in order to separate or transect a body part
terms.explanation: All or a portion of the body part is separated into two or more portions

title: Drainage
terms.definition: Taking or letting out fluids and/or gases from a body part
terms.explanation: The qualifier DIAGNOSTIC is used to identify drainage procedures that are biopsies

title: Excision
terms.definition: Cutting out or off, without replacement, a portion of a body part
terms.explanation: The qualifier DIAGNOSTIC is used to identify excision procedures that are biopsies

title: Extirpation
terms.definition: Taking or cutting out solid matter from a body part
terms.explanation: The solid matter may be an abnormal byproduct of a biological function or a foreign body; it may be imbedded in a body part or in the lumen of a tubular body part. The solid matter may or may not have been previously broken into pieces

title: Extraction
terms.definition: Pulling or stripping out or off all or a portion of a body part by the use of force
terms.explanation: The qualifier DIAGNOSTIC is used to identify extraction procedures that are biopsies

title: Fragmentation
terms.definition: Breaking solid matter in a body part into pieces
terms.explanation: Physical force (e.g., manual, ultrasonic) applied directly or indirectly is used to break the solid matter into pieces. The solid matter may be an abnormal byproduct of a biological function or a foreign body. The pieces of solid matter are not taken out

title: Fusion
terms.definition: Joining together portions of an articular body part rendering the articular body part immobile
terms.explanation: The body part is joined together by fixation device, bone graft, or other means

title: Insertion
terms.definition: Putting in a nonbiological appliance that monitors, assists, performs, or prevents a physiological function but does not physically take the place of a body part
includes: Insertion of radioactive implant, insertion of central venous catheter

title: Inspection
terms.definition: Visually and/or manually exploring a body part
terms.explanation: Visual exploration may be performed with or without optical instrumentation. Manual exploration may be performed directly or through intervening body layers

title: Map
terms.definition: Locating the route of passage of electrical impulses and/or locating functional areas in a body part
terms.explanation: Applicable only to the cardiac conduction mechanism and the central nervous system

title: Occlusion
terms.definition: Completely closing an orifice or the lumen of a tubular body part
terms.explanation: The orifice can be a natural orifice or an artificially created orifice
includes: Fallopian tube ligation, ligation of inferior vena cava

title: Reattachment
terms.definition: Putting back in or on all or a portion of a separated body part to its normal location or other suitable location
terms.explanation: Vascular circulation and nervous pathways may or may not be reestablished
includes: Reattachment of hand, reattachment of avulsed kidney

title: Release
terms.definition: Freeing a body part from an abnormal physical constraint by cutting or by the use of force
terms.explanation: Some of the restraining tissue may be taken out but none of the body part is taken out

title: Removal
terms.definition: Taking out or off a device from a body part
terms.explanation: If a device is taken out and a similar device put in without cutting or puncturing the skin or mucous membrane, the procedure is coded to the root operation CHANGE. Otherwise, the procedure for taking out a device is coded to the root operation REMOVAL
includes: Drainage tube removal, cardiac pacemaker removal

title: Repair
terms.definition: Restoring, to the extent possible, a body part to its normal anatomic structure and function
terms.explanation: Used only when the method to accomplish the repair is not one of the other root operations

title: Replacement
terms.definition: Putting in or on biological or synthetic material that physically takes the place and/or function of all or a portion of a body part
terms.explanation: The body part may have been taken out or replaced, or may be taken out, physically eradicated, or rendered nonfunctional during the Replacement procedure. A Removal procedure is coded for taking out the device used in a previous replacement procedure
includes: Total hip replacement, bone graft, free skin graft

title: Reposition
terms.definition: Moving to its normal location, or other suitable location, all or a portion of a body part
terms.explanation: The body part is moved to a new location from an abnormal location, or from a normal location where it is not functioning correctly. The body part may or may not be cut out or off to be moved to the new location
includes: Reposition of undescended testicle, fracture reduction

title: Resection
terms.definition: Cutting out or off, without replacement, all of a body part
includes: Total nephrectomy, total lobectomy of lung

title: Restriction
terms.definition: Partially closing an orifice or the lumen of a tubular body part
terms.explanation: The orifice can be a natural orifice or an artificially created orifice

title: Revision
terms.definition: Correcting, to the extent possible, a portion of a malfunctioning device or the position of a displaced device
terms.explanation: Revision can include correcting a malfunctioning or displaced device by taking out or putting in components of the device such as a screw or pin
includes: Adjustment of position of pacemaker lead, recementing of hip prosthesis

title: Supplement
terms.definition: Putting in or on biological or synthetic material that physically reinforces and/or augments the function of a portion of a body part
terms.explanation: The biological material is non-living, or is living and from the same individual. The body part may have been previously replaced, and the Supplement procedure is performed to physically reinforce and/or augment the function of the replaced body part
includes: Herniorrhaphy using mesh, mitral valve ring annuloplasty, put a new acetabular liner in a previous hip replacement

title: Transfer
terms.definition: Moving, without taking out, all or a portion of a body part to another location to take over the function of all or a portion of a body part
terms.explanation: The body part transferred remains connected to its vascular and nervous supply
includes: Tendon transfer, skin pedicle flap transfer

title: Transplantation
terms.definition: Putting in or on all or a portion of a living body part taken from another individual or animal to physically take the place and/or function of all or a portion of a similar body part
terms.explanation: The native body part may or may not be taken out, and the transplanted body part may take over all or a portion of its function

title: Fluoroscopy

title: Magnetic Resonance Imaging (MRI)

title: Systemic Nuclear Medicine Therapy

title: Alternate Binaural or Monaural Loudness Balance
terms.definition: Determines auditory stimulus parameter that yields the same objective sensation
includes: Sound intensities that yield same loudness perception

title: Anthropometric Characteristics
terms.definition: Measures edema, body fat composition, height, weight, length and girth

title: Aphasia (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures expressive and receptive speech and language function including reading and writing

title: Aphasia (Treatment)
terms.definition: Applying techniques to improve, augment, or compensate for receptive/ expressive language impairments

title: Articulation/Phonology (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures speech production

title: Articulation/Phonology (Treatment)
terms.definition: Applying techniques to correct, improve, or compensate for speech productive impairment

title: Assistive Listening Device
terms.definition: Assists in use of effective and appropriate assistive listening device/system

title: Assistive Listening System/Device Selection
terms.definition: Measures the effectiveness and appropriateness of assistive listening systems/devices

title: Assistive, Adaptive, Supportive or Protective Devices
terms.explanation: Devices to facilitate or support achievement of a higher level of function in wheelchair mobility; bed mobility; transfer or ambulation ability; bath and showering ability; dressing; grooming; personal hygiene; play or leisure

title: Auditory Evoked Potentials
terms.definition: Measures electric responses produced by the VIIIth cranial nerve and brainstem following auditory stimulation

title: Auditory Processing (Assessment)
terms.definition: Evaluates ability to receive and process auditory information and comprehension of spoken language

title: Auditory Processing (Treatment)
terms.definition: Applying techniques to improve the receiving and processing of auditory information and comprehension of spoken language

title: Augmentative/Alternative Communication System (Assessment)
terms.definition: Determines the appropriateness of aids, techniques, symbols, and/or strategies to augment or replace speech and enhance communication
includes: Includes the use of telephones, writing equipment, emergency equipment, and TDD

title: Augmentative/Alternative Communication System (Treatment)
includes: Includes augmentative communication devices and aids

title: Aural Rehabilitation
terms.definition: Applying techniques to improve the communication abilities associated with hearing loss

title: Aural Rehabilitation Status
terms.definition: Measures impact of a hearing loss including evaluation of receptive and expressive communication skills

title: Bathing/Showering
includes: Includes obtaining and using supplies; soaping, rinsing, and drying body parts; maintaining bathing position; and transferring to and from bathing positions

title: Bathing/Showering Techniques
terms.definition: Activities to facilitate obtaining and using supplies, soaping, rinsing and drying body parts, maintaining bathing position, and transferring to and from bathing positions

title: Bed Mobility (Assessment)
terms.definition: Transitional movement within bed

title: Bed Mobility (Treatment)
terms.definition: Exercise or activities to facilitate transitional movements within bed

title: Bedside Swallowing and Oral Function
includes: Bedside swallowing includes assessment of sucking, masticating, coughing, and swallowing.  Oral function includes assessment of musculature for controlled movements, structures and functions to determine coordination and phonation

title: Bekesy Audiometry
terms.definition: Uses an instrument that provides a choice of discrete or continuously varying pure tones; choice of pulsed or continuous signal

title: Binaural Electroacoustic Hearing Aid Check
terms.definition: Determines mechanical and electroacoustic function of bilateral hearing aids using hearing aid test box

title: Binaural Hearing Aid (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures the candidacy, effectiveness, and appropriateness of a hearing aids
terms.explanation: Measures bilateral fit

title: Binaural Hearing Aid (Treatment)
terms.explanation: Assists in achieving maximum understanding and performance

title: Bithermal, Binaural Caloric Irrigation
terms.definition: Measures the rhythmic eye movements stimulated by changing the temperature of the vestibular system

title: Bithermal, Monaural Caloric Irrigation
terms.definition: Measures the rhythmic eye movements stimulated by changing the temperature of the vestibular system in one ear

title: Brief Tone Stimuli
terms.definition: Measures specific central auditory process

title: Cerumen Management
terms.definition: Includes examination of external auditory canal and tympanic membrane and removal of cerumen from external ear canal

title: Cochlear Implant
terms.definition: Measures candidacy for cochlear implant

title: Cochlear Implant Rehabilitation
terms.definition: Applying techniques to improve the communication abilities of individuals with cochlear implant; includes programming the device, providing patients/families with information

title: Communicative/Cognitive Integration Skills (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures ability to use higher cortical functions
includes: Includes orientation, recognition, attention span, initiation and termination of activity, memory, sequencing, categorizing, concept formation, spatial operations, judgment, problem solving, generalization and pragmatic communication

title: Communicative/Cognitive Integration Skills (Treatment)
terms.definition: Activities to facilitate the use of higher cortical functions
includes: Includes level of arousal, orientation, recognition, attention span, initiation and termination of activity, memory sequencing,  judgment and problem solving, learning and generalization, and pragmatic communication

title: Computerized Dynamic Posturography
terms.definition: Measures the status of the peripheral and central vestibular system and the sensory/motor component of balance; evaluates the efficacy of vestibular rehabilitation

title: Conditioned Play Audiometry
terms.definition: Behavioral measures using nonspeech and speech stimuli to obtain frequency-specific and ear-specific information on auditory status from the patient
terms.explanation: Obtains speech reception threshold by having patient point to pictures of spondaic words

title: Coordination/Dexterity (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures large and small muscle groups for controlled goal- directed movements
terms.explanation: Dexterity includes object manipulation

title: Coordination/Dexterity (Treatment)
terms.definition: Exercise or activities to facilitate gross coordination and fine coordination

title: Cranial Nerve Integrity
terms.definition: Measures cranial nerve sensory and motor functions, including tastes, smell and facial expression

title: Dichotic Stimuli
terms.definition: Measures specific central auditory process

title: Distorted Speech
terms.definition: Measures specific central auditory process

title: Dix-Hallpike Dynamic
terms.definition: Measures nystagmus following Dix-Hallpike maneuver

title: Dressing
includes: Includes selecting clothing and accessories, obtaining clothing from storage, dressing and, fastening and adjusting clothing and shoes, and applying and removing personal devices, prosthesis or orthosis

title: Dressing Techniques
terms.definition: Activities to facilitate selecting clothing and accessories, dressing and undressing, adjusting clothing and shoes, applying and removing devices, prostheses or orthoses

title: Dynamic Orthosis
includes: Includes customized and prefabricated splints, inhibitory casts, spinal and other braces, and protective devices; allows motion through transfer of movement from other body parts or by use of outside forces

title: Ear Canal Probe Microphone
terms.definition: Real ear measures

title: Ear Protector Attentuation
terms.definition: Measures ear protector fit and effectiveness

title: Electrocochleography
terms.definition: Measures the VIIIth cranial nerve action potential

title: Environmental, Home and Work Barriers
terms.definition: Measures current and potential barriers to optimal function, including safety hazards, access problems and home or office design

title: Ergonomics and Body Mechanics
terms.definition: Ergonomic measurement of job tasks, work hardening or work conditioning needs; functional capacity; and body mechanics

title: Eustachian Tube Function
terms.definition: Measures eustachian tube function and patency of eustachian tube

title: Evoked Otoacoustic Emissions, Diagnostic
terms.definition: Measures auditory evoked potentials in a diagnostic format

title: Evoked Otoacoustic Emissions, Screening
terms.definition: Measures auditory evoked potentials in a screening format

title: Facial Nerve Function
terms.definition: Measures electrical activity of the VIIth cranial nerve (facial nerve)

title: Feeding/Eating (Assessment)
includes: Includes setting up food, selecting and using utensils and tableware, bringing food or drink to mouth, cleaning face, hands, and clothing, and management of alternative methods of nourishment

title: Feeding/Eating (Treatment)
terms.definition: Exercise or activities to facilitate setting up food, selecting and using utensils and tableware, bringing food or drink to mouth, cleaning face, hands, and clothing, and management of alternative methods of nourishment

title: Filtered Speech
terms.definition: Uses high or low pass filtered speech stimuli to assess central auditory processing disorders, site of lesion testing

title: Fluency (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures speech fluency or stuttering

title: Fluency (Treatment)
terms.definition: Applying techniques to improve and augment fluent speech

title: Gait and/or Balance
terms.definition: Measures biomechanical, arthrokinematic and other spatial and temporal characteristics of gait and balance

title: Gait Training/Functional Ambulation
terms.definition: Exercise or activities to facilitate ambulation on a variety of surfaces and in a variety of environments

title: Grooming/Personal Hygiene (Assessment)
includes: Includes ability to obtain and use supplies in a sequential fashion, general grooming, oral hygiene, toilet hygiene, personal care devices, including care for artificial airways

title: Grooming/Personal Hygiene (Treatment)
terms.definition: Activities to facilitate obtaining and using supplies in a sequential fashion: general grooming, oral hygiene, toilet hygiene, cleaning body, and personal care devices, including artificial airways

title: Hearing and Related Disorders Counseling
terms.definition: Provides patients/families/caregivers with information, support, referrals to facilitate recovery from a communication disorder
includes: Includes strategies for psychosocial adjustment to hearing loss for clients and families/caregivers

title: Hearing and Related Disorders Prevention
terms.definition: Provides patients/families/caregivers with information and support to prevent communication disorders

title: Hearing Screening
terms.definition: Pass/refer measures designed to identify need for further audiologic assessment

title: Home Management (Assessment)
terms.definition: Obtaining and maintaining personal and household possessions and environment
includes: Includes clothing care, cleaning, meal preparation and cleanup, shopping, money management, household maintenance, safety procedures, and childcare/parenting

title: Home Management (Treatment)
terms.definition: Activities to facilitate obtaining and maintaining personal household possessions and environment
includes: Includes clothing care, cleaning, meal preparation and clean-up, shopping, money management, household maintenance, safety procedures, childcare/parenting

title: Instrumental Swallowing and Oral Function
terms.definition: Measures swallowing function using instrumental diagnostic procedures
terms.explanation: Methods include videofluoroscopy, ultrasound, manometry, endoscopy

title: Integumentary Integrity
includes: Includes burns, skin conditions, ecchymosis, bleeding, blisters, scar tissue, wounds and other traumas, tissue mobility, turgor and texture

title: Manual Therapy Techniques
terms.definition: Techniques in which the therapist uses his/her hands to administer skilled movements
includes: Includes connective tissue massage, joint mobilization and manipulation, manual lymph drainage, manual traction, soft tissue mobilization and manipulation

title: Masking Patterns
terms.definition: Measures central auditory processing status

title: Monaural Electroacoustic Hearing Aid Check
terms.definition: Determines mechanical and electroacoustic function of one hearing aid using hearing aid test box

title: Monaural Hearing Aid (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures the candidacy, effectiveness, and appropriateness of a hearing aid
terms.explanation: Measures unilateral fit

title: Monaural Hearing Aid (Treatment)
terms.explanation: Assists in achieving maximum understanding and performance

title: Motor Function (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures the body's functional and versatile movement patterns
includes: Includes motor assessment scales, analysis of head, trunk and limb movement, and assessment of motor learning

title: Motor Function (Treatment)
terms.definition: Exercise or activities to facilitate crossing midline, laterality, bilateral integration, praxis, neuromuscular relaxation, inhibition, facilitation, motor function and motor learning

title: Motor Speech (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures neurological motor aspects of speech production

title: Motor Speech (Treatment)
terms.definition: Applying techniques to improve and augment the impaired neurological motor aspects of speech production

title: Muscle Performance (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures muscle strength, power and endurance using manual testing, dynamometry or computer-assisted electromechanical muscle test; functional muscle strength, power and endurance; muscle pain, tone, or soreness; or pelvic-floor musculature
terms.explanation: Muscle endurance refers to the ability to contract a muscle repeatedly over time

title: Muscle Performance (Treatment)
terms.definition: Exercise or activities to increase the capacity of a muscle to do work in terms of strength, power, and/or endurance
terms.explanation: Muscle strength is the force exerted to overcome resistance in one maximal effort. Muscle power is work produced per unit of time, or the product of strength and speed. Muscle endurance is the ability to contract a muscle repeatedly over time

title: Neuromotor Development
terms.definition: Measures motor development, righting and equilibrium reactions, and reflex and equilibrium reactions

title: Non-invasive Instrumental Status
terms.definition: Instrumental measures of oral, nasal, vocal, and velopharyngeal functions as they pertain to speech production

title: Nonspoken Language (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures nonspoken language (print, sign, symbols) for communication

title: Nonspoken Language (Treatment)
terms.definition: Applying techniques that improve, augment, or compensate spoken communication

title: Oral Peripheral Mechanism
terms.definition: Structural measures of face, jaw, lips, tongue, teeth, hard and soft palate, pharynx as related to speech production

title: Orofacial Myofunctional (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures orofacial myofunctional patterns for speech and related functions

title: Orofacial Myofunctional (Treatment)
terms.definition: Applying techniques to improve, alter, or augment impaired orofacial myofunctional patterns and related speech production errors

title: Oscillating Tracking
terms.definition: Measures ability to visually track

title: Pain
terms.definition: Measures muscle soreness, pain and soreness with joint movement, and pain perception
includes: Includes questionnaires, graphs, symptom magnification scales or visual analog scales

title: Perceptual Processing (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures stereognosis, kinesthesia, body schema, right-left discrimination, form constancy, position in space, visual closure, figure-ground, depth perception, spatial relations and topographical orientation

title: Perceptual Processing (Treatment)
terms.definition: Exercise and activities to facilitate perceptual processing
terms.explanation: Includes stereognosis, kinesthesia, body schema, right-left discrimination, form constancy, position in space, visual closure, figure-ground, depth perception, spatial relations, and topographical orientation
includes: Includes stereognosis, kinesthesia, body schema, right-left discrimination, form constancy, position in space, visual closure, figure-ground, depth perception, spatial relations, and topographical orientation

title: Performance Intensity Phonetically Balanced Speech Discrimination
terms.definition: Measures word recognition over varying intensity levels

title: Postural Control
terms.definition: Exercise or activities to increase postural alignment and control

title: Prosthesis
terms.definition: Artificial substitutes for missing body parts that augment performance or function

title: Psychosocial Skills (Assessment)
terms.definition: The ability to interact in society and to process emotions
includes: Includes psychological (values, interests, self-concept); social (role performance, social conduct, interpersonal skills, self expression); self-management (coping skills, time management, self-control)

title: Psychosocial Skills (Treatment)
terms.definition: The ability to interact in society and to process emotions
includes: Includes psychological (values, interests, self-concept); social (role performance, social conduct, interpersonal skills, self expression); self-management (coping skills, time management, self-control)

title: Pure Tone Audiometry, Air
terms.definition: Air-conduction pure tone threshold measures with appropriate masking

title: Pure Tone Audiometry, Air and Bone
terms.definition: Air-conduction and bone-conduction pure tone threshold measures with appropriate masking

title: Pure Tone Stenger
terms.definition: Measures unilateral nonorganic hearing loss based on simultaneous presentation of pure tones of differing volume

title: Range of Motion and Joint Integrity
terms.definition: Measures quantity, quality, grade, and classification of joint movement and/or mobility
terms.explanation: Range of Motion is the space, distance or angle through which movement occurs at a joint or series of joints.  Joint integrity is the conformance of joints to expected anatomic, biomechanical and kinematic norms

title: Range of Motion and Joint Mobility
terms.definition: Exercise or activities to increase muscle length and joint mobility

title: Receptive/Expressive Language (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures receptive and expressive language

title: Receptive/Expressive Language (Treatment)
terms.definition: Applying techniques tot improve and augment receptive/expressive language

title: Reflex Integrity
terms.definition: Measures the presence, absence, or exaggeration of developmentally appropriate, pathologic or normal reflexes

title: Select Picture Audiometry
terms.definition: Establishes hearing threshold levels for speech using pictures

title: Sensorineural Acuity Level
terms.definition: Measures sensorineural acuity masking presented via bone conduction

title: Sensory Aids
terms.definition: Determines the appropriateness of a sensory prosthetic device, other than a hearing aid or assistive listening system/device

title: Sensory Awareness/Processing/Integrity
includes: Includes light touch, pressure, temperature, pain, sharp/dull, proprioception, vestibular, visual, auditory, gustatory, and olfactory

title: Short Increment Sensitivity Index
terms.definition: Measures the ear's ability to detect small intensity changes; site of lesion test requiring a behavioral response

title: Sinusoidal Vertical Axis Rotational
terms.definition: Measures nystagmus following rotation

title: Somatosensory Evoked Potentials
terms.definition: Measures neural activity from sites throughout the body

title: Speech and/or Language Screening
terms.definition: Identifies need for further speech and/or language evaluation

title: Speech Threshold
terms.definition: Measures minimal intensity needed to repeat spondaic words

title: Speech-Language Pathology and Related Disorders Counseling
terms.definition: Provides patients/families with information, support, referrals to facilitate recovery from a communication disorder

title: Speech-Language Pathology and Related Disorders Prevention
terms.definition: Applying techniques to avoid or minimize onset and/or development of a communication disorder

title: Speech/Word Recognition
terms.definition: Measures ability to repeat/identify single syllable words; scores given as a percentage; includes word recognition/speech discrimination

title: Staggered Spondaic Word
terms.definition: Measures central auditory processing site of lesion based upon dichotic presentation of spondaic words

title: Static Orthosis
includes: Includes customized and prefabricated splints, inhibitory casts, spinal and other braces, and protective devices; has no moving parts, maintains joint(s) in desired position

title: Stenger
terms.definition: Measures unilateral nonorganic hearing loss based on simultaneous presentation of signals of differing volume

title: Swallowing Dysfunction
terms.definition: Activities to improve swallowing function in coordination with respiratory function
includes: Includes function and coordination of sucking, mastication, coughing, swallowing

title: Synthetic Sentence Identification
terms.definition: Measures central auditory dysfunction using identification of third order approximations of sentences and competing messages

title: Temporal Ordering of Stimuli
terms.definition: Measures specific central auditory process

title: Therapeutic Exercise
terms.definition: Exercise or activities to facilitate sensory awareness, sensory processing, sensory integration, balance training, conditioning, reconditioning
includes: Includes developmental activities, breathing exercises, aerobic endurance activities, aquatic exercises, stretching and ventilatory muscle training

title: Tinnitus Masker (Assessment)
terms.definition: Determines candidacy for tinnitus masker

title: Tinnitus Masker (Treatment)
terms.explanation: Used to verify physical fit, acoustic appropriateness, and benefit; assists in achieving maximum benefit

title: Tone Decay
terms.definition: Measures decrease in hearing sensitivity to a tone; site of lesion test requiring a behavioral response

title: Transfer
terms.definition: Transitional movement from one surface to another

title: Transfer Training
terms.definition: Exercise or activities to facilitate movement from one surface to another

title: Tympanometry
terms.definition: Measures the integrity of the middle ear; measures ease at which sound flows through the tympanic membrane while air pressure against the membrane is varied

title: Unithermal Binaural Screen
terms.definition: Measures the rhythmic eye movements stimulated by changing the temperature of the vestibular system  in both ears using warm water, screening format

title: Ventilation, Respiration and Circulation
terms.definition: Measures ventilatory muscle strength, power and endurance, pulmonary function and ventilatory mechanics
includes: Includes ability to clear airway, activities that aggravate or relieve edema, pain, dyspnea or other symptoms, chest wall mobility, cardiopulmonary response to performance of ADL and IAD, cough and sputum, standard vital signs

title: Vestibular
terms.definition: Applying techniques to compensate for balance disorders; includes habituation, exercise therapy, and balance retraining

title: Visual Motor Integration (Assessment)
terms.definition: Coordinating the interaction of information from the eyes with body movement during activity

title: Visual Motor Integration (Treatment)
terms.definition: Exercise or activities to facilitate coordinating the interaction of information from eyes with body movement during activity

title: Visual Reinforcement Audiometry
terms.definition: Behavioral measures using nonspeech and speech stimuli to obtain frequency/ear-specific information on auditory status
includes: Includes a conditioned response of looking toward a visual reinforcer (e.g., lights, animated toy) every time auditory stimuli are heard

title: Vocational Activities and Functional Community or Work Reintegration Skills (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures environmental, home, work (job/school/play) barriers that keep patients from functioning optimally in their environment
includes: Includes assessment of vocational skill and interests, environment of work (job/school/play), injury potential and injury prevention or reduction, ergonomic stressors, transportation skills, and ability to access and use community resources

title: Vocational Activities and Functional Community or Work Reintegration Skills (Treatment)
terms.definition: Activities to facilitate vocational exploration, body mechanics training, job acquisition, and environmental or work (job/school/play) task adaptation
includes: Includes injury prevention and reduction, ergonomic stressor reduction, job coaching and simulation, work hardening and conditioning, driving training, transportation skills,  and use of community resources

title: Voice (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures vocal structure, function and production

title: Voice (Treatment)
terms.definition: Applying techniques to improve voice and vocal function

title: Voice Prosthetic (Assessment)
terms.definition: Determines the appropriateness of voice prosthetic/adaptive device to enhance or facilitate communication

title: Voice Prosthetic (Treatment)
includes: Includes electrolarynx, and other assistive, adaptive, supportive devices

title: Wheelchair Mobility (Assessment)
terms.definition: Measures fit and functional abilities within wheelchair in a variety of environments

title: Wheelchair Mobility (Treatment)
terms.definition: Management, maintenance and controlled operation of a wheelchair, scooter or other device, in and on a variety of surfaces and environments

title: Wound Management
includes: Includes non-selective and selective debridement (enzymes, autolysis, sharp debridement), dressings (wound coverings, hydrogel, vacuum-assisted closure), topical agents, etc.

title: Biofeedback
terms.definition: Provision of information from the monitoring and regulating of physiological processes in conjunction with cognitive-behavioral techniques to improve patient functioning or well-being
includes: Includes EEG, blood pressure, skin temperature or peripheral blood flow, ECG, electrooculogram, EMG, respirometry or capnometry, GSR/EDR, perineometry to monitor/regulate bowel/bladder activity, electrogastrogram to monitor/regulate gastric motility

title: Counseling
terms.definition: The application of psychological methods to treat an individual with normal developmental issues and psychological problems in order to increase function, improve well-being, alleviate distress, maladjustment or resolve crises

title: Crisis Intervention
terms.definition: Treatment of a traumatized, acutely disturbed or distressed individual for the purpose of short-term stabilization
includes: Includes defusing, debriefing, counseling, psychotherapy and/or coordination of care with other providers or agencies

title: Electroconvulsive Therapy
terms.definition: The application of controlled electrical voltages to treat a mental health disorder
includes: Includes appropriate sedation and other preparation of the individual

title: Family Psychotherapy
terms.definition: Treatment that includes one or more family members of an individual with a mental health disorder by behavioral, cognitive, psychoanalytic, psychodynamic or psychophysiological means to improve functioning or well-being
terms.explanation: Remediation of emotional or behavioral problems presented by one or more family members in cases where psychotherapy with more than one family member is indicated

title: Group Psychotherapy
terms.definition: Treatment of two or more individuals with a mental health disorder by behavioral, cognitive, psychoanalytic, psychodynamic or psychophysiological means to improve functioning or well-being

title: Hypnosis
terms.definition: Induction of a state of heightened suggestibility by auditory, visual and tactile techniques to elicit an emotional or behavioral response

title: Individual Psychotherapy
terms.definition: Treatment of an individual with a mental health disorder by behavioral, cognitive, psychoanalytic, psychodynamic or psychophysiological means to improve functioning or well-being

title: Light Therapy
terms.definition: Application of specialized light treatments to improve functioning or well-being

title: Medication Management
terms.definition: Monitoring and adjusting the use of medications for the treatment of a mental health disorder

title: Narcosynthesis
terms.definition: Administration of intravenous barbiturates in order to release suppressed or repressed thoughts

title: Psychological Tests
terms.definition: The administration and interpretation of standardized psychological tests and measurement instruments for the assessment of psychological function

title: Behavioral
terms.definition: Primarily to modify behavior
includes: Includes modeling and role playing, positive reinforcement of target behaviors, response cost, and training of self-management skills

title: Cognitive
terms.definition: Primarily to correct cognitive distortions and errors

title: Cognitive-Behavioral
terms.definition: Combining cognitive and behavioral treatment strategies to improve functioning
terms.explanation: Maladaptive responses are examined to determine how cognitions relate to behavior patterns in response to an event. Uses learning principles and information-processing models

title: Developmental
terms.definition: Age-normed developmental status of cognitive, social and adaptive behavior skills

title: Intellectual and Psychoeducational
terms.definition: Intellectual abilities, academic   achievement and learning capabilities (including behaviors and emotional factors affecting learning

title: Interactive
terms.definition: Uses primarily physical aids and other forms of non-oral interaction with a patient who is physically, psychologically or developmentally unable to use ordinary language for communication
includes: Includes. the use of toys in symbolic play

title: Interpersonal
terms.definition: Helps an individual make changes in interpersonal behaviors to reduce psychological dysfunction
includes: Includes exploratory techniques, encouragement of affective expression, clarification of patient statements, analysis of communication patterns, use of therapy relationship and behavior change techniques

title: Neurobehavioral and Cognitive Status
terms.definition: Includes neurobehavioral status exam, interview(s), and observation for the clinical assessment of thinking, reasoning and judgment, acquired knowledge, attention, memory, visual spatial abilities, language functions, and planning

title: Neuropsychological
terms.definition: Thinking, reasoning and judgment, acquired knowledge, attention, memory, visual spatial abilities, language functions, planning

title: Personality and Behavioral
terms.definition: Mood, emotion, behavior, social functioning, psychopathological conditions, personality traits and characteristics

title: Psychoanalysis
terms.definition: Methods of obtaining a detailed account of past and present mental and emotional experiences to determine the source and eliminate or diminish the undesirable effects of unconscious conflicts
terms.explanation: Accomplished by making the individual aware of their existence, origin, and inappropriate expression in emotions and behavior

title: Psychodynamic
terms.definition: Exploration of past and present emotional experiences to understand motives and drives using insight-oriented techniques to reduce the undesirable effects of internal conflicts on emotions and behavior
terms.explanation: Techniques include empathetic listening, clarifying self-defeating behavior patterns, and exploring adaptive alternatives

title: Psychophysiological
terms.definition: Monitoring and alteration of physiological processes to help the individual associate physiological reactions combined with cognitive and behavioral strategies to gain improved control of these processes to help the individual cope more effectively

title: Supportive
terms.definition: Formation of therapeutic relationship primarily for providing emotional support to prevent further deterioration in functioning during periods of particular stress
terms.explanation: Often used in conjunction with other therapeutic approaches

title: Vocational
terms.definition: Exploration of vocational interests, aptitudes and required adaptive behavior skills to develop and carry out a plan for achieving a successful vocational placement
includes: Includes enhancing work related adjustment and/or pursuing viable options in training education or preparation

title: Detoxification Services
terms.definition: Detoxification from alcohol and/or drugs
terms.explanation: Not a treatment modality, but helps the patient stabilize physically and psychologically until the body becomes free of drugs and the effects of alcohol

title: Family Counseling
terms.definition: The application of psychological methods that includes one or more family members to treat an individual with addictive behavior
terms.explanation: Provides support and education for family members of addicted individuals. Family member participation is seen as a critical area of substance abuse treatment

title: Group Counseling
terms.definition: The application of psychological methods to treat two or more individuals with addictive behavior
terms.explanation: Provides structured group counseling sessions and healing power through the connection with others

title: Individual Counseling
terms.definition: The application of psychological methods to treat an individual with addictive behavior
terms.explanation: Comprised of several different techniques, which apply various strategies to address drug addiction

title: Individual Psychotherapy
terms.definition: Treatment of an individual with addictive behavior by behavioral, cognitive, psychoanalytic, psychodynamic or psychophysiological means

title: Medication Management
terms.definition: Monitoring and adjusting the use of replacement medications for the treatment of addiction

title: Pharmacotherapy
terms.definition: The use of replacement medications for the treatment of addiction

title: Assistance
terms.definition: Taking over a portion of a physiological function by extracorporeal means

title: Destruction
terms.definition: Physical eradication of all or a portion of a body part by the direct use of energy, force, or a destructive agent
terms.explanation: None of the body part is physically taken out
includes: Fulguration of rectal polyp, cautery of skin lesion

title: Dilation
terms.definition: Expanding an orifice or the lumen of a tubular body part
terms.explanation: The orifice can be a natural orifice or an artificially created orifice. Accomplished by stretching a tubular body part using intraluminal pressure or by cutting part of the orifice or wall of the tubular body part

title: Extirpation
terms.definition: Taking or cutting out solid matter from a body part
terms.explanation: The solid matter may be an abnormal byproduct of a biological function or a foreign body; it may be imbedded in a body part or in the lumen of a tubular body part. The solid matter may or may not have been previously broken into pieces

title: Fusion
terms.definition: Joining together portions of an articular body part rendering the articular body part immobile
terms.explanation: The body part is joined together by fixation device, bone graft, or other means

title: Introduction
terms.definition: Putting in or on a therapeutic, diagnostic, nutritional, physiological, or prophylactic substance except blood or blood products

title: Measurement
terms.definition: Determining the level of a physiological or physical function at a point in time

title: Monitoring
terms.definition: Determining the level of a physiological or physical function repetitively over a period of time

title: Replacement
terms.definition: Putting in or on biological or synthetic material that physically takes the place and/or function of all or a portion of a body part
terms.explanation: The body part may have been taken out or replaced, or may be taken out, physically eradicated, or rendered nonfunctional during the Replacement procedure. A Removal procedure is coded for taking out the device used in a previous replacement procedure
includes: Total hip replacement, bone graft, free skin graft

title: Reposition
terms.definition: Moving to its normal location, or other suitable location, all or a portion of a body part
terms.explanation: The body part is moved to a new location from an abnormal location, or from a normal location where it is not functioning correctly. The body part may or may not be cut out or off to be moved to the new location
includes: Reposition of undescended testicle, fracture reduction

title: Supplement
terms.definition: Putting in or on biological or synthetic material that physically reinforces and/or augments the function of a portion of a body part

title: Transfusion
terms.definition: Putting in blood or blood products

title: External
terms.definition: Procedures performed directly on the skin or mucous membrane and procedures performed indirectly by the application of external force through the skin or mucous membrane

title: Open
terms.definition: Cutting through the skin or mucous membrane and any other body layers necessary to expose the site of the procedure

title: Percutaneous
terms.definition: Entry, by puncture or minor incision, of instrumentation through the skin or mucous membrane and any other body layers necessary to reach the site of the procedure

title: Percutaneous Endoscopic
terms.definition: Entry, by puncture or minor incision, of instrumentation through the skin or mucous membrane and any other body layers necessary to reach and visualize the site of the procedure

title: Via Natural or Artificial Opening
